					<description><![CDATA[<p>Funding Supports Clinical Development Plans Ona Therapeutics has raised an $86.6 million oversubscribed Series B funding round that will finance the progression of its antibody-drug conjugate (ADC) pipeline in treatment-resistant</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/ona-therapeutics-raises-86-6m-to-advance-cancer-adc-pipeline/" data-wpel-link="internal">Ona Therapeutics Raises $86.6M to Advance Cancer ADC Pipeline</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Funding Supports Clinical Development Plans</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Ona Therapeutics has raised an $86.6 million oversubscribed Series B funding round that will finance the progression of its antibody-drug conjugate (ADC) pipeline in treatment-resistant cancers. The round was co-led by Columbus Venture Partners and Mrieux Equity Partners and included contributions from COFIDES, Korys and its existing investors.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The Barcelona-based biotechnology company designs first-in-class ADCs that aim to selectively and effectively target cancer cells, increasing the potential for positive treatment outcomes and minimizing side effects. Ona claims its patented platform has the potential to overcome significant barriers to successful treatment of drug resistant tumors.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funds raised will predominantly fuel the clinical progression of ONA-255, the company&#8217;s lead program in breast cancer. Ona plans to achieve clinical proof of concept, and to demonstrate both the safety and efficacy of this treatment in patient. Positive results may give ONA-255 an important advantage within the competitive oncology field.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funds will also allow ONA-389 to move towards first-in-human studies. The drug candidate targets colorectal cancer, a disease that has and continues to pose an enormous threat, leading to a disproportionate number of cancer deaths globally. Better treatments are still required and there is a particular need for them for patients whose therapeutic options have run out.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Ona maintains full global commercial rights to all its programs, giving it discretion over any potential future partnerships and commercialization options. This also provides it with a greater degree of autonomy over the direction of the development of its pipeline programs.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">CEO, Valerie Vanhooren called the financing &#8220;an incredibly exciting moment&#8221;. She stated that this investment will help to &#8220;accelerate our efforts and reiterate our commitment to the many patients with limited or no treatment options&#8221; and acknowledged the high quality of the investors who participated in the Series B funding round.</span></p>
<h2><b>Proprietary Platform Targets Drug Resistance</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Ona Therapeutics was created to tackle one of oncology’s most difficult challenges. Many cancers eventually develop resistance to existing treatments. This can reduce effectiveness and limit options for patients. The company’s scientific approach focuses on identifying tumour-specific </span><a href="https://my.clevelandclinic.org/health/diseases/24067-antigen" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">antigens</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> linked to resistance biology and advanced disease.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Its proprietary patient-driven discovery platform helps researchers identify novel targets for ADC development. These targets enable highly efficient delivery of therapeutic payloads directly into cancer cells. The approach is designed to maximise anti-tumour activity while reducing toxicity to healthy tissues.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Unlike traditional treatments that may affect healthy cells, ADCs combine targeted antibodies with cancer-killing agents. This allows drugs to reach tumours more precisely. As interest in ADC technology continues to grow, several biotechnology companies are racing to develop next-generation treatments.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Ona’s lead programme, ONA-255, has generated encouraging preclinical results. The therapy is specifically designed to address treatment-resistant tumour biology. The company believes its differentiated mechanism could improve the therapeutic index compared with previous approaches.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Meanwhile, ONA-389 is expanding the company’s presence into colorectal cancer. Additional research efforts are also exploring opportunities in gastric and liver cancers. These indications represent areas where significant unmet medical needs remain.</span></p>
<h2><b>Investor Confidence Reflects Growing Momentum</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_202385" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202385" class="size-full wp-image-202385" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Ona-2.png" alt="Illustration of oncology biotech innovation supported by global investor networks, showing cancer research pipelines, clinical development, and strong institutional backing." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-202385" class="wp-caption-text">Investor confidence is accelerating oncology innovation, with strong institutional backing supporting advanced cancer research, clinical development pipelines, and experienced leadership guiding the path toward differentiated therapeutic breakthroughs. Source: Created by Ventureburn.</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The financing attracted support from both new and existing investors. Columbus Venture Partners and Mérieux Equity Partners joined as co-lead investors. Existing backers including Alta Life Sciences, Asabys Partners, Bpifrance, CDTI through SICC Innvierte, FundPlus NV and Ysios Capital also participated.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Jose Mesa of Columbus Venture Partners said Ona combines strong science with a clear route towards clinical impact. He pointed to the company’s work on cancer resistance and metastasis as an important opportunity within oncology. The firm believes the pipeline has the potential to support a differentiated cancer treatment platform.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Valérie Calenda of Mérieux Equity Partners highlighted the strength of the company’s scientific foundation. She noted that the quality of preclinical data and focused development strategy contributed to investor confidence. Both executives are expected to join Ona’s Board of Directors following the financing.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s leadership team brings significant experience in oncology drug development. Board Chair Antoine Yver has extensive expertise in global cancer therapeutics. Independent Board Member Pamela Klein has also played key roles in advancing oncology treatments. Their experience is expected to support the company during upcoming clinical milestones.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/coralogix-raises-200m-to-scale-ai-native-observability-platform/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Coralogix Raises $200M to Scale AI Native Observability Platform</span></a></p>
<h2><b>Building the Next Generation of Cancer Therapies</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This new investment will come at a critical time for Ona Therapeutics. The company is about to start moving from pre-clinical development into clinical trials and success at this stage could massively raise the profile and valuation of its programmes and attract significant further strategic interest. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The ADC market remains of massive interest to investors with many pharmaceutical groups keen to identify the best new novel treatments for the treatment of resistant cancers, a need for greater targeting specificity in cancer therapeutics is a major driver as attempts are made to improve clinical outcomes whilst reducing treatment associated toxicity. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Ona Therapeutics takes a novel combined biological discovery, antibody engineering and payload design platform to enable it to design and develop novel therapies, hoping to achieve and deliver clinically meaningful patient benefit and is confident it will be able to continue to build future programs on top of its current portfolio. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With additional investment secured Ona Therapeutics can now look to deliver the scientific promise into patient outcomes with future success for its lead programs ONA-255 and ONA-389 being a key focus for investors for years to come.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/ona-therapeutics-raises-86-6m-to-advance-cancer-adc-pipeline/" data-wpel-link="internal">Ona Therapeutics Raises $86.6M to Advance Cancer ADC Pipeline</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
