										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>What Is Kalshi?</b></h2>
<p><a href="https://kalshi.com/" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Kalshi</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> is a regulated prediction market where users can trade event outcomes just like financial assets. It’s not a casino or gambling platform. Kalshi works under U.S. government regulation, providing a safe and compliant environment for people to trade on real-world events. Instead of trading stocks or crypto tokens, users trade on whether certain events will happen or not.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Imagine turning your opinions into opportunities. If you believe a specific event will occur, you can buy contracts that pay out if you’re right. Whether you predict political shifts, inflation rates, or crypto market moves, Kalshi gives people a way to profit from their knowledge and insights.</span></p>
<p>Kalshi&#8217;s goal is to empower everyone, not just financial experts, by turning everyday news and global events into tradable investment opportunities.</p>
<div id="attachment_193895" style="width: 751px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-193895" class="wp-image-193895" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/kalshi1.jpg" alt="What Is Kalshi?" width="741" height="417" /><p id="caption-attachment-193895" class="wp-caption-text">Source: X</p></div>
<h3><b>An Unprecedented Asset Class: Event Contracts</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Kalshi created something completely new — event contracts. These contracts work like a bridge between news and finance. Each contract represents a “Yes” or “No” outcome for a specific event. If the event happens, the “Yes” contracts settle at $1. If not, they settle at $0.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This structure makes trading simple and fair. You don’t need to understand complex financial tools. You just need to decide what you believe will happen. Will the next election result favor one party? Will Bitcoin close above $70,000 this month? Each prediction becomes a tradable market.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">By turning opinions into tradable contracts, Kalshi has given rise to a new type of asset class. This innovation has drawn the attention of traders, investors, and institutions worldwide.</span></p>
<h3><b>Leveling the Playing Field</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">For years, advanced trading and risk management tools were limited to big institutions. Ordinary investors couldn’t hedge against real-world risks or capitalize on their insights in a structured way. Kalshi changes that.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Through event contracts, Kalshi allows anyone to participate in markets that reflect their understanding of world events. Whether it’s an investor hedging against inflation or a crypto enthusiast predicting market shifts, everyone gets equal access.</span></p>
<p>This strategy has made Kalshi a democratizing force, giving the general public access to the same sophisticated financial tools previously reserved for professionals.</p>
<h3><b>A Marketplace of Ideas</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Think of Kalshi as a marketplace for ideas. Instead of trading shares of companies, users trade the outcomes of events that matter most to them. From politics to weather patterns and crypto price predictions, Kalshi lets people engage with topics that affect their lives.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This turns information into opportunity. If you follow the news closely or have deep knowledge about a subject, you can use it to trade effectively. Kalshi transforms discussions about “what might happen” into measurable and tradable probabilities.</span></p>
<h3><b>The Power of Yes and No</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">At its core, Kalshi operates on a simple question: Will it happen or not?</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br />
</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Each market has two sides — “Yes” and “No.” This design keeps things straightforward and user-friendly. Even beginners can participate without feeling overwhelmed.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you think an event will occur, you buy “Yes.” If not, you buy “No.” The simplicity makes it easy to understand your position and potential outcome.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Kalshi’s binary trading structure removes confusion and makes the platform accessible for everyone — from casual users to seasoned traders.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_193896" style="width: 1510px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-193896" class="wp-image-193896 size-full" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/kalshi2.jpg" alt="The Power of Yes and No" width="1500" height="500" /><p id="caption-attachment-193896" class="wp-caption-text">Source: X</p></div>
<h2><b>How Does Kalshi Work?</b></h2>
<p>Kalshi works as a neutral exchange platform. Users often ask <b data-path-to-node="11,1,1,0" data-index-in-node="62">is Kalshi decentralized</b> or <b data-path-to-node="11,1,1,0" data-index-in-node="89">is Kalshi blockchain based</b>? Unlike a typical <b data-path-to-node="11,1,1,0" data-index-in-node="134">Kalshi blockchain</b> project, the platform is a centralized, CFTC-regulated exchange, not a betting site.</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The company makes money from transaction fees, not from taking sides on contracts. This structure keeps Kalshi impartial and transparent. Every transaction follows clear rules under CFTC supervision, ensuring trust and reliability.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Kalshi charges low, competitive fees so users keep most of their profits. Their fee system is publicly available, showing exactly how much users pay and why. This openness has built trust within their growing community.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_193897" style="width: 1144px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-193897" class="wp-image-193897 size-full" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/kalshi3.jpg" alt="How Does Kalshi Work?" width="1134" height="720" /><p id="caption-attachment-193897" class="wp-caption-text">Source: X</p></div>
<h2><b>Kalshi Team</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">It was founded in 2018 by </span><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/mansourtarek/" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Tarek Mansour </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">and </span><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/luana-lopes-lara-3151068a/" data-wpel-link="external" rel="external noopener noreferrer"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Luana Lopes Lara</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. The two met while studying at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT). With backgrounds in financial analysis, they wanted to make financial hedging more accessible for everyday investors.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The idea for Kalshi came during major global events like the Brexit referendum. Many investors struggled to hedge their positions against such uncertainties. Mansour and Lopes Lara realized there needed to be a way for people to trade directly on events themselves — not just on assets affected by them.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Their shared vision turned into Kalshi, now one of the most recognized prediction markets in the financial and crypto space.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_193898" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-193898" class="wp-image-193898 size-full" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/kalshi4.jpg" alt="Kalshi Team" width="1024" height="683" /><p id="caption-attachment-193898" class="wp-caption-text">Source: X</p></div>
<h2><b>Kalshi Token</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">At this time, this information is not accessible. As soon as additional information is available, VentureBurn will offer an update.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Kalshi has not formally confirmed a token release, despite several outside websites speculating about it. The CFTC regulates it, therefore a <b data-path-to-node="14,1,1,0" data-index-in-node="36">Kalshi token airdrop</b> might make compliance difficult. For those wondering <b data-path-to-node="14,1,1,0" data-index-in-node="110">is Kalshi crypto based</b>, note that it currently uses fiat currency (USD) instead of implementing a token system just yet.</span></p>
<h2><b>Kalshi Fundings</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Kalshi has seen major support from some of the most respected investors in finance and crypto.</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">In February 2021, Kalshi raised $30 million in its Series A round, led by Sequoia Capital.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">In June 2025, it secured $185 million in Series C funding led by Paradigm, with participation from Sequoia, Multicoin, Neo, and BOND Capital. This round pushed Kalshi’s valuation to $2 billion.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Later, in August 2025, Kalshi closed its Series D round worth over $300 million, led by Sequoia Capital and Andreessen Horowitz (a16z). Other investors included Paradigm, Coinbase Ventures, CapitalG, Spark Capital, and General Catalyst.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">After this round, Kalshi’s valuation rose to around $5 billion, making it one of the best-funded prediction platforms in the world.</span></p>
<h2><b>Kalshi Roadmap</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Growth and accessibility are the main focuses of Kalshi&#8217;s roadmap. The company intends to forge closer ties with leading brokerages and cryptocurrency apps in addition to growing into more than 140 countries. It keeps enhancing the user experience, trading speed, and liquidity.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Kalshi has made significant progress in integrating with the cryptocurrency ecosystem, despite not having revealed a token or airdrop. Instead than jumping headfirst into token releases, the emphasis is still on offering dependable, regulated event trading.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_193899" style="width: 610px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-193899" class="wp-image-193899 size-full" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/kalshi5.jpg" alt="Kalshi Roadmap" width="600" height="400" /><p id="caption-attachment-193899" class="wp-caption-text">Source: X</p></div>
<h2><b>Kalshi Klear</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">A major step in Kalshi’s progress is the creation of Kalshi Klear, a proprietary clearinghouse for its markets. Previously, Kalshi’s contracts were cleared by MIAXdx. Now, Kalshi Klear handles the process directly, approved by the Commodity Futures Trading Commission (CFTC).</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Kalshi Klear speeds up everything. It supports faster listings, quicker settlements, and smoother performance. Traders get payouts sooner, and the system can respond faster to breaking news. It also introduces 3.75% APY interest on holdings, allowing users’ funds to grow even while they trade.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Kalshi Klear represents a major technical upgrade, making Kalshi’s trading environment faster, more efficient, and more rewarding.</span></p>
<h2><b>How To Get Kalshi Airdrop?</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">At this time, this information is not accessible. As soon as additional information is available, VentureBurn will offer an update.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">In the event of a future airdrop, you would probably need to register on the official site, validate your account, and take part fully. For updates, it&#8217;s essential to stick to Kalshi&#8217;s verified communication channels and stay away from illegitimate links or claims until then.</span></p>
<h2><b>Kalshi Review: Final Thoughts</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Kalshi is changing the way that individuals trade based on global events. Event-based trading is made safe and professional by fusing regulated finance with cutting-edge prediction markets. With the support of leading investors and cutting-edge technology like Kalshi Klear, the platform provides a degree of legitimacy that few rivals can match.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">However, cryptocurrency users seeking decentralized features or community-driven incentives may find Kalshi less interesting due to its absence of a token or airdrop. Nevertheless, it is one of the most dependable platforms for prediction-based trading available today due to its well-established reputation and regulated structure.</span></p>
<p><b>Advantages</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The main benefit of Kalshi is its governmental accreditation, which reassures users that their trades are safe and authentic. It also provides a large selection of event markets, ranging from cryptocurrency forecasts to economics, which appeals to a variety of traders.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Long-term growth and financial stability are guaranteed by the significant investors&#8217; unwavering support. For users who prefer digital payments, the incorporation of cryptocurrency deposits like Bitcoin and Solana also increases flexibility.</span></p>
<p><b>Disadvantages</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The absence of a native token on Kalshi restricts participation from cryptocurrency traders who profit from token-based incentives. Additionally, users in areas with restricted financial access may be deterred by its stringent KYC procedure.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Although decentralized platforms like Zeitgeist and Polymarket provide greater independence, they lack the same level of regulatory protection. Users are protected by Kalshi&#8217;s compliance, but it may hinder the platform&#8217;s ability to evolve.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Notwithstanding these shortcomings, Kalshi is a reliable and strong exchange that is popularizing prediction trading.</span></p>
