					<description><![CDATA[<p>Quobly has officially closed a massive €115 million ($125 million) Series A funding round. The extraordinary fundraising achievement is one of the largest early-stage raises of all time in the</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/quobly-closes-e115m-series-a-for-quantum-growth/" data-wpel-link="internal">Quobly Closes €115M Series A for Quantum Growth</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="https://www.quobly.io/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">Quobly </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">has officially closed a massive €115 million ($125 million) Series A </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/gigaton-raises-26m-to-transform-industrial-control/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">funding </span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">round. The extraordinary fundraising achievement is one of the largest early-stage raises of all time in the worldwide quantum industry and will enable the French startup to take on industry behemoths in the competition to create a fault-tolerant, commercial quantum computer.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The oversubscribed round was led by the strong consortium of European deep tech and institutional investors comprising the European Innovation Council (EIC) Fund, Bpifrance and various international venture capital investors experienced in frontier technology.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new capital will be used to hire more engineering staff to increase Quobly&#8217;s proprietary design automation software and, finally, to deliver Quobly&#8217;s first pilot high-fidelity quantum processors.</span></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">The Silicon Advantage: Leveraging Existing Mega-Factories</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founded in 2022 as a spinoff of the internationally acclaimed research bodies CEA, Leti and CNRS, Quobly is pursuing a radically pragmatic approach to the problem of quantum supremacy. Unlike other quantum architectures that use exotic and hard-to-scale technologies like superconducting loops, trapped ions or neutral atoms, Quobly’s design starts from silicon spin qubits.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Through the use of off-the-shelf silicon transistors, Quobly is able to build quantum processors using off-the-shelf semiconductor foundries. This industrial-first approach enables the startup to instantaneously leap over the multibillion-dollar infrastructural bottleneck facing all competing quantum modalities.</span></p>
<div id="attachment_202371" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202371" class="size-large wp-image-202371" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/cube-shaped-building-1024x606.jpg" alt="cube shaped building" width="1024" height="606" /><p id="caption-attachment-202371" class="wp-caption-text">Source: Unsplash</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;The fundamental barrier to useful quantum computing is scalability, going from dozens of qubits to millions,&#8221; said Maud Vinet, co-founder and CEO of Quobly. &#8220;Rival technologies require entirely new manufacturing paradigms. We are utilising the multi-trillion-dollar silicon manufacturing ecosystem that the world has optimised over the last fifty years. This €115 million investment proves that our investors recognise silicon as the only viable highway to millions of physical qubits.&#8221;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/gigaton-raises-26m-to-transform-industrial-control/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Gigaton Raises $26M to Transform Industrial Control</span></a></p>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">Bridging the Gap to Fault Tolerance</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">A primary technological hurdle in quantum computing is environmental noise, which induces decoherence, a state where fragile qubits lose their quantum information, resulting in calculation errors. To achieve true commercial utility, quantum computers require millions of physical qubits working together via complex error-correction codes to create stable logical qubits.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Quobly&#8217;s proprietary design optimises standard silicon-on-insulator transistors to manipulate the spin of individual electrons trapped inside the silicon channel. Because these spin qubits are remarkably compact and measure only a few nanometres across, Quobly can densely pack thousands of qubits onto a single square millimetre of a standard microchip.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The €115 million capital injection will be heavily weaponised across three core strategic domains:</span></p>
<ol>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Foundry Integration:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Solidifying manufacturing partnerships with leading global semiconductor foundries to transition its prototype qubit designs into high-volume, commercial silicon wafers.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Cryogenic Control Electronics:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Developing integrated control circuitry capable of managing thousands of high-speed spin qubits at ultra-low, near-absolute-zero temperatures.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400"><b>Software Stack Development:</b><span style="font-weight: 400"> Expanding its Quantum Computer-Aided Design (Q-CAD) platform, enabling engineers to model, simulate, and optimize massive silicon qubit layouts before sending them to the foundry.</span></li>
</ol>
<h2><span style="font-weight: 400">A Sovereign Win for European Deep Tech</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Beyond the staggering financial metrics, Quobly&#8217;s €115 million Series A represents a significant geopolitical milestone for European technological sovereignty. As the United States and China aggressively fund domestic quantum initiatives, the European Union has actively prioritized the creation of local deep-tech flagships.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">By anchoring its operations in Grenoble, Quobly draws directly from a massive local talent pool of semiconductor engineers, physicists, and cleanroom facilities. The massive funding ensures that Europe retains a leading operational stake in the core hardware infrastructure that will define the next century of materials science, cryptography, and molecular medicine.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">&#8220;Quobly is sitting at the precise intersection of quantum physics and advanced semiconductor manufacturing,&#8221; noted a lead investor from Bpifrance. &#8220;They aren&#8217;t trying to reinvent the factory; they are reinventing the microchip. This round gives them the financial runway and muscle needed to move from a brilliant scientific breakthrough to a dominant global hardware standard.&#8221;</span></p>
